The paper proposes a computational framework that assesses cognitive engagement in real-time using EEG signals as objective measurements. This involves the use of a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) and a sliding window method. The application of this framework is in rehabilitation robots, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning techniques such as CNNs and the sliding window method suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the framework to rehabilitation robots suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and cybernetics (cs.CYBER).
